dict-documentation.doc-line: This file contains all the monitor points and trigger data that is used
to Fire Alterts using alert intelligence
help "Text to look for in the ipmitool sdr"
the field can contain either numeric data such as temperature or Fan RPM
(type N for numeric) or it may contain just an OK/Not OK value in the case of
the ipmi reading file should contain the date,time, sensor name in the first
three fields. the data field may be in any field from 4 onwards.
This field contains the field number in the file. Field number 1 is the first
help "The number of the field that contains the value"
help "Enter T if the boolean match text will result in TRUE or F for false"
The program looks at fields marked as boolean. It looks at the text in this
field. If it matches the text in the IPMI then the value is set to TRUE.
if not the value is set to FALSE.
Triggers are raised when the value of the field is false.
So the description for a redundant power supply sensor should be
"Power supply OK". The reading true value should be "ok". Whenever
the reading returns something other than OK. Then the value is set
to FALSE and a trigger alarm raised.
